n class="mrow" id="MathJax-Span-569"><span class="mo" id="MathJax-Span-570"><span style="font-family: STIXGeneral, 'Arial Unicode MS', serif; font-size: 81%; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;">含</span></span></span></span><span class="texatom" id="MathJax-Span-571"><span class="mrow" id="MathJax-Span-572"><span class="mo" id="MathJax-Span-573"><span style="font-family: STIXGeneral, 'Arial Unicode MS', serif; font-size: 81%; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;">对</span></span></span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; height: 2.543em;"></span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: -0.309em; border-left-width: 0px; border-left-style: solid; width: 0px; height: 1.378em;"></span></span></nobr><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>还</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>是</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>不</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>相</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>等</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>的</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>。</mo></mrow><mi>ε</mi><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>中</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>可</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>能</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>包</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>含</mo></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mo>对</mo></mrow></math></span></span><script type="math/tex" id="MathJax-Element-49">还是不相等的。\varepsilon中可能包含对</script>Y$有影响的变量——但我们并未观察或者无法观察，亦或是，这个复杂世界中所不可避免的各种微小因素。</p>

<p>考虑给定的\hat f和给定的观测变量X时，E(Y-\hat{Y})^{2} = E[f(X) + \varepsilon - \hat{f}(x)]^2=\underbrace{[f(X) - \hat{f}(X)]^2} + \underbrace{Var(\varepsilon)}</p>

<p>前半部分是可约误差——可以通过不断寻找更接近真实<span class="MathJax_Preview" style="color: inherit;"></span><span class="MathJax" id="MathJax-Element-50-Frame" tabindex="0" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;" role="presentation" style="position: relative;"><nobr aria-hidden="true"><span class="math" id="MathJax-Span-574" role="math" style="width: 0.561em; display: inline-block;"><span style="display: inline-block; position: relative; width: 0.46em; height: 0px; font-size: 123%;"><span style="position: absolute; clip: rect(1.73em, 1000.46em, 2.899em, -999.997em); top: -2.538em; left: 0.003em;"><span class="mrow" id="MathJax-Span-575"><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-576" style="font-family: STIXGeneral-Italic;">f<span style="display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; height: 1px; width: 0.155em;"></span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; height: 2.543em;"></span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: -0.309em; border-left-width: 0px; border-left-style: solid; width: 0px; height: 1.191em;"></span></span></nobr><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi></math></span></span><script type="math/tex" id="MathJax-Element-50">f</script>的\hat f来减少，后半部分是不可约误差——那就好好忽略它吧; )</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>不可约误差提供了预测精度的一个上界，这个上界在实践中是未知的。</p>
</blockquote>

<p>上述角度来源于「预测」——关注误差重于一切，实际上是更偏向于工程的角度，这块的发展也由实际需求在不断推动。还有一种角度更关心的则是「推断」——X与Y之间的关系到底是怎样的？Y如何被X以怎样的程度影响...</p>

<p>预测还是推断，这个对于模型的构建非常重要。例如，若为了推断，往往采用的是参数模型，最简单的就是线性模型，变量之间的相互影响一目了然。</p>
